5. Ratio (multiplied by 100) of price index for gross domestic product
to the price index for gross domestic purchases.
6. Ratio (multiplied by 100) of the price index for exports of goods
and services to the price index for imports of goods and services.
7. Ratio (multiplied by 100) of the price index for goods exports
to the price index for goods imports.

to the price index for nonpetroleum goods imports.
